msgstr "**CĂłdigo-fonte:** :source:`Lib/signal.py`"

#: ../../library/signal.rst:11
msgid "This module provides mechanisms to use signal handlers in Python."
msgstr ""
"Este mĂłdulo fornece mecanismos para usar manipuladores de sinal em Python."

#: ../../library/signal.rst:15
msgid "General rules"
msgstr "Regras gerais"

#: ../../library/signal.rst:17
msgid ""
"The :func:`signal.signal` function allows defining custom handlers to be "
"executed when a signal is received.  A small number of default handlers are "
"installed: :const:`SIGPIPE` is ignored (so write errors on pipes and sockets "
"can be reported as ordinary Python exceptions) and :const:`SIGINT` is "
"translated into a :exc:`KeyboardInterrupt` exception if the parent process "
"has not changed it."
msgstr ""
"A funĂ§ĂŁo :func:`signal.signal` permite definir manipuladores personalizados "
"a serem executados quando um sinal ĂŠ recebido. Um pequeno nĂşmero de "
"manipuladores padrĂŁo sĂŁo instalados: :const:`SIGPIPE` ĂŠ ignorado (entĂŁo "
"erros de gravaĂ§ĂŁo em encadeamentos e sockets podem ser relatados como "
"exceĂ§Ăľes comuns do Python) e :const:`SIGINT` ĂŠ traduzido em uma exceĂ§ĂŁo :exc:"
"`KeyboardInterrupt` se o processo pai nĂŁo a tiver alterado."

#: ../../library/signal.rst:24
msgid ""
"A handler for a particular signal, once set, remains installed until it is "
"explicitly reset (Python emulates the BSD style interface regardless of the "
"underlying implementation), with the exception of the handler for :const:"
"`SIGCHLD`, which follows the underlying implementation."
msgstr ""
"Um manipulador para um sinal especĂ­fico, uma vez definido, permanece "
"instalado atĂŠ ser explicitamente redefinido (o Python emula a interface de "
"estilo BSD independentemente da implementaĂ§ĂŁo subjacente), com exceĂ§ĂŁo do "
"manipulador para :const:`SIGCHLD`, que segue a implementaĂ§ĂŁo subjacente."

#: ../../library/signal.rst:29
msgid ""
"On WebAssembly platforms, signals are emulated and therefore behave "
"differently. Several functions and signals are not available on these "
"platforms."
msgstr ""
"Em plataformas WebAssembly, os sinais sĂŁo emulados e, portanto, se comportam "
"de forma diferente. VĂĄrias funĂ§Ăľes e sinais nĂŁo estĂŁo disponĂ­veis nessas "
"plataformas."

#: ../../library/signal.rst:34
msgid "Execution of Python signal handlers"
msgstr "ExecuĂ§ĂŁo de manipuladores de sinais Python"

#: ../../library/signal.rst:36
msgid ""
"A Python signal handler does not get executed inside the low-level (C) "
"signal handler.  Instead, the low-level signal handler sets a flag which "
"tells the :term:`virtual machine` to execute the corresponding Python signal "
"handler at a later point (for example, at the next :term:`bytecode` "
"instruction). This has consequences:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../library/signal.rst:42
msgid ""
"It makes little sense to catch synchronous errors like :const:`SIGFPE` or :"
"const:`SIGSEGV` that are caused by an invalid operation in C code.  Python "
"will return from the signal handler to the C code, which is likely to raise "
"the same signal again, causing Python to apparently hang.  From Python 3.3 "
"onwards, you can use the :mod:`faulthandler` module to report on synchronous "
"errors."
msgstr ""
"Faz pouco sentido capturar erros sĂ­ncronos como :const:`SIGFPE` ou :const:"
"`SIGSEGV` que sĂŁo causados por uma operaĂ§ĂŁo invĂĄlida no cĂłdigo C. O Python "
"retornarĂĄ do manipulador de sinais para o cĂłdigo C, o que provavelmente "
"levantarĂĄ o mesmo sinal novamente, fazendo com que o Python aparentemente "
"trave. Do Python 3.3 em diante, vocĂŞ pode usar o mĂłdulo :mod:`faulthandler` "
"para relatar erros sĂ­ncronos."

#: ../../library/signal.rst:49
msgid ""
"A long-running calculation implemented purely in C (such as regular "
"expression matching on a large body of text) may run uninterrupted for an "
"arbitrary amount of time, regardless of any signals received.  The Python "
"signal handlers will be called when the calculation finishes."
msgstr ""
"Um cĂĄlculo de longa duraĂ§ĂŁo implementado puramente em C (como "
"correspondĂŞncia de expressĂŁo regular em um grande corpo de texto) pode ser "
"executado ininterruptamente por um perĂ­odo de tempo arbitrĂĄrio, "
"independentemente de quaisquer sinais recebidos. Os manipuladores de sinal "
"do Python serĂŁo chamados quando o cĂĄlculo terminar."

#: ../../library/signal.rst:54
msgid ""
"If the handler raises an exception, it will be raised \"out of thin air\" in "
"the main thread. See the :ref:`note below <handlers-and-exceptions>` for a "
"discussion."
msgstr ""
"Se o manipulador levantar uma exceĂ§ĂŁo, ela serĂĄ levantada \"do nada\" na "
"thread principal. Veja a :ref:`nota abaixo <handlers-and-exceptions>` para "
"uma discussĂŁo."

#: ../../library/signal.rst:62
msgid "Signals and threads"
msgstr "Sinais e threads"

#: ../../library/signal.rst:64
msgid ""
"Python signal handlers are always executed in the main Python thread of the "
"main interpreter, even if the signal was received in another thread.  This "
"means that signals can't be used as a means of inter-thread communication.  "
"You can use the synchronization primitives from the :mod:`threading` module "
"instead."
msgstr ""
"Os manipuladores de sinais Python sĂŁo sempre executados na thread principal "
"do Python do interpretador principal, mesmo se o sinal foi recebido em outra "
"thread. Isso significa que os sinais nĂŁo podem ser usados como um meio de "
"comunicaĂ§ĂŁo entre threads. VocĂŞ pode usar as primitivas de sincronizaĂ§ĂŁo do "
"mĂłdulo :mod:`threading` em vez disso."

#: ../../library/signal.rst:69
msgid ""
"Besides, only the main thread of the main interpreter is allowed to set a "
"new signal handler."
msgstr ""
"AlĂŠm disso, somente a thread principal do interpretador principal tem "
"permissĂŁo para definir um novo manipulador de sinal."

#: ../../library/signal.rst:73
msgid ""
"Synchronization primitives such as :class:`threading.Lock` should not be "
"used within signal handlers.  Doing so can lead to unexpected deadlocks."
msgstr ""

